  abstract =	 "We study the joint processes of job mobility and wage
		  growth among young men drawn from the     Longitudinal
		  Employee-Employer Data. Following individuals at three
		  month intervals from     their entry into the labor
		  market, we track career patterns of job changing and the
		  evolution of     wages for up to 15 years. Following an
		  initial period of weak attachment to both the labor force
		  and particular employers, careers tend to stabilize in
		  the sense of strong labor force attachment     and
